    <div class="card-body">
      <h5>Team Communication</h5>
      <div class="card-text">
        <p>Contributing to team communication</p>
        <p>
          <ul>
            <li><i>Constructive criticism</i> - All positions should be able to both give and receive constructive criticism in a respectful manner, and in the proper context (i.e. pull requests, peer reviews, etc.)</li>
            <li><i>Debate instead of argue</i> - The manner in which all positions resolve conflict should be level headed and respectful.</li>
            <li><i>Honesty</i> - Willing to say “I don’t know” when appropriate.  Supports an environment of trust and openness.</li>
            <li><i>Timely</i> - Responds clearly to team messages (e.g. Email, Slack, PR Review, etc.) in a timely manner whether in or out of the office.  Responds clearly to meeting requests and attends meetings on time.</li>
          </ul>
        </p>
        <div class="field form-group">
          <table class="table">
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row"><%= f.radio_button(:teaming_score,"0",{:style => "min-height: 2rem; min-width: 2rem;", :class => "form-control"}) %></th>
                <td>Fails to meet minimum expectations</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row"><%= f.radio_button(:teaming_score,"1",{:style => "min-height: 2rem; min-width: 2rem;", :class => "form-control"}) %></th>
                <td>
                  <p class="mb-0">Participates in discussions when asked or needed</p>
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row"><%= f.radio_button(:teaming_score,"2",{:style => "min-height: 2rem; min-width: 2rem;", :class => "form-control"}) %></th>
                <td>
                  <p class="mb-0">Actively participates in discussions</p>
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row"><%= f.radio_button(:teaming_score,"3",{:style => "min-height: 2rem; min-width: 2rem;", :class => "form-control"}) %></th>
                <td>
                  <p class="mb-0">Facilitates team discussions and encourages team members to contribute to the best of their abilities</p>
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row"><%= f.radio_button(:teaming_score,"4",{:style => "min-height: 2rem; min-width: 2rem;", :class => "form-control"}) %></th>
                <td>
                  <p class="mb-0">Recognizes the need for and seizes the opportunity to instigate team and departmental discussions of relevant topics. Guarantees that all voices are heard, and that conversation remains constructive.
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row"><%= f.radio_button(:teaming_score,"5",{:style => "min-height: 2rem; min-width: 2rem;", :class => "form-control"}) %></th>
                <td>
                  <p>Vastly exceeds all expectations</p>
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="text-center"><%= button_tag image_tag("open-iconic/svg/ban.svg", size: "16"), id: 'review_teaming_score_clear', type: 'button', onclick: "document.getElementById('review_teaming_score_0').checked = false; document.getElementById('review_teaming_score_1').checked = false; document.getElementById('review_teaming_score_2').checked = false; document.getElementById('review_teaming_score_3').checked = false; document.getElementById('review_teaming_score_4').checked = false; document.getElementById('review_teaming_score_5').checked = false;", class: 'btn btn-light' %></th>
                <td>
                  <p>Clear Selection</p>
                </td>
              </tr>
           </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
  
      <div class="field form-group">
        <%= f.label :teaming_notes, "Comments" %>
        <%= f.text_area :teaming_notes, size: "40x5", class: "form-control" %>
      </div>
